Property Receptionist/Secretary
Confidential Company - ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/06 10:48:33
Ref. JB3047836
Job Description
Reception
• First point of contact on main reception desk; greeting and welcoming visitors.
• Answering all incoming telephone calls, transferring to relevant extensions.
• Taking accurate messages and relaying via e-mail to appropriate member of staff.
• Making telephone calls.
• Making appointments.
• Maintaining, recording and retrieving answer-machine messages.
• Recording and maintaining visitors’ book and staff whereabouts.
• Receiving and directing deliveries to the office.
• Sending and receiving/distributing fax correspondence.
• Opening and distribution incoming mail.
• Preparing documents for out-going mail in readiness for collection.
• Maintaining up-to-date postal information/services.
• Use of franking machine and a knowledge of postal rates.
• Monitoring and re-ordering stationery and other office consumables.
• Overseeing and maintaining meeting room booking requests.
• Binding documents . annual accounts, letting agreements.
• Inputting and maintaining Land Factor timesheets.
Filing
• Electronic filing of documents.
• Filing hard copies of documents.
• Maintaining up-to-date filing system.
• Taking control and recording in transferring live to archive files.
• Archiving/Retrieval of “dead files”. Security shredding.
General Administration
• Attend regular secretaries meetings and take minutes.
• Photocopying/binding/shredding.
• Making coffee/tea for meetings etc (as required).
• General office procedures.
• Plus any other duties that may be necessary
Skills
Audio/copy typing
• Typing a variety of Microsoft Word documents including letters, reports etc
• Use of digital dictation software.
• Creating mail merge documents and setting up and maintaining data sources using Microsoft
Access.
• Creating reports and spreadsheets using Microsoft Excel.
• Proof-reading to ensure that all documentation is finalised to a high standard.
Microsoft Outlook
• Making appointments and maintaining calendar.
• Arranging appointments for managers and external customers.
• Sending and receiving email correspondence.
• Use of other Outlook functions.
PA Duties
• Organising travel arrangements.
• Booking venues.
• Making and receiving telephone calls on behalf of Manager.
Team Organisation:
• Provide support in organising and prioritising Manager and Assistant work loads.
• Organise, attend and contribute to meetings to predict and plan work loads.
• Take control of bring forward systems.
Finance/STAR
• Preparing monthly financial reports for Manager/team meetings.
• Preparing reports for ongoing professional jobs.
• Creating billing requests and preparing draft invoices for finalization.
• Creating various financial reports.
Repairs
• Receiving and logging incoming repairs.
• Taking instructions from Manager and instructing and liaising with sub-contractors.
• Preparing repair reports and arranging and contributing to team repair meetings.
• Monitoring work in progress.
• Liaising with tenants.
• Preparing and ensuring all relevant paperwork is correct and up-to-date.
Lettings
• Preparing particulars for vacant properties and co-ordinating advertising.
• Collating and recording data on prospective tenants and arranging viewings etc.
• Preparation of all documents including agreements associated with tenancies.
• Inputting and maintaining data in Agreements database.
• Liaise with Manager regarding rent demands/tenancy reminders prior to Estateman deadlines.
• Organizing Energy Performance Certificates for marketed properties.
Education
General Administration
